        public BreadBotBuilder addStaticPrefix(java.lang.String prefix)
        Description copied from interface: CommandPluginBuilder
        This adds a module that implements PrefixPlugin to provide a static prefix that cannot be changed. If a PrefixPlugin is not added, one will be provided with a static prefix of "!"

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultPrefixModule(prefix))

        You can define a different prefix implementation by providing an object to addModule(ICommandModule) that implements IPrefixModule

      • addOwnerPlugin

        public BreadBotBuilder addOwnerPlugin(long... owners)
        Description copied from interface: CommandPluginBuilder
        Allows the @Owner annotation to be used. If one or more ids are provided as an argument to this method, then only those id's are recognized as being able to use a command marked with @Owner. If no ids are provided to this method, the only owner recognized is the application owner.

      • addAdminPlugin

        public BreadBotBuilder addAdminPlugin()
        Description copied from interface: CommandPluginBuilder
        This enables the @Admin annotation that is marked on Command classes. This ensures that Commands marked with @Admin are only usable by Administrators.

        It is important to include an implementation of AdminModule through either this method, addAdminPlugin(Predicate), or your own implementation. Otherwise, all users will have access to Administrative Commands

        The default criteria for defining an Administrator is as follows:

        • Has Kick Members Permission
        • Is higher than the bot on the role hierarchy

        Different criteria to determine which member has administrative status with addAdminPlugin(Predicate) or your own implementation of AdminPlugin

        Specified by:
        addAdminPlugin in interface CommandPluginBuilder
        Returns:
        this

      • addCommandModifier

        public <T> BreadBotBuilder addCommandModifier(java.lang.Class<T> propertyType,
                                              java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,CommandHandleBuilder> configurator)
        Description copied from interface: CommandPropertiesManager
        The provided configurator is used to modify commands that possess the specified property. This behavior is added onto any existing behavior. When a command is registered with that property (usually an annotation), the provided configurator is applied. If there are already commands registered, the configurator is applied to those as well.
        Specified by:
        addCommandModifier in interface CommandPropertiesManager
        Type Parameters:
        T - the propertyType
        Parameters:

        configurator - a BiConsumer. The first argument is the property. The second argument is the CommandHandleBuilder the property is attached to.
